<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,151,218]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,151,177]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Eberle" authorityYear="2010" box="[599,685,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Xenorthrius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lanatus">
<emphasis box="[599,685,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">lanatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a Latin adjective meaning woolly, refers to the woolly pilosity of the mesosternum.
</paragraph>
